EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to common-interest communities; enacting provisions relating to
the installation and maintenance of electric vehicle charging stations
within a common-interest community; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the unit-owners’ association of a common-interest community to
2 adopt bylaws and authorizes an association to amend bylaws and adopt rules and regulations
3 relating to the community. (NRS 116.3102) This bill: (1) authorizes an association to install
4 an electric vehicle charging station [in a] on the common [area] elements under certain
5 circumstances; (2) authorizes an association to enter into a necessary contract for the
6 installation or maintenance of an electric vehicle charging station [in a] on the common [area]
7 elements after complying with certain requirements; and (3) provides that the installation and
8 maintenance of an electric vehicle charging station [in a] on the common [area] elements
9 shall be deemed not to constitute a change in use of the common [area,] elements, a
10 commercial use of the common [area] elements or a capital improvement.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 116 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 1. Notwithstanding any provision in the governing documents or this
4 chapter to the contrary:
5 (a) An association may install an electric vehicle charging station [in a] on
6 the common [area] elements if:
7 (1) The location [in] on the common [area] elements is not being used
8 for recreation, including, without limitation, being used as a park, playground or
9 open play space;
10 (2) [A majority of the units’ owners, whether present in person or by
11 proxy, do not reject the proposed electric vehicle charging station by vote at a

