10 (b) An association may, after complying with the provisions of
11 subparagraphs (1) to (4), inclusive, of paragraph (a), enter into any necessary
12 contract with any person for the installation or maintenance of an electric vehicle
13 charging station [in a] on the common [area.] elements.
14 (c) The installation and maintenance of an electric vehicle charging station
15 [in a] on the common [area] elements shall be deemed not to constitute:
16 (1) A change in use of the common [area;] elements;
17 (2) A commercial use of the common [area;] elements; or
18 (3) A capital improvement.
19 2. Within 60 days after the executive board decides to install an electric
20 vehicle charging station on the common elements pursuant to this section, the
21 executive board shall notify each unit’s owner of the decision and shall set a date
22 for a meeting of the units’ owners to consider ratification of the decision not less
23 than 14 days or more than 30 days after notifying the units’ owners. Unless at
24 that meeting a majority of all units’ owners reject the decision of the executive
25 board to install an electric vehicle charging station on the common elements, the
26 decision of the executive board is ratified, whether or not a quorum is present.
27 3. If the decision of the executive board to install an electric vehicle
28 charging station on the common elements is ratified by the units’ owners
29 pursuant to subsection 2 and the association will be responsible for the operation
30 of the electric vehicle charging station, then the association may adopt rules and
31 regulations governing the use of the electric vehicle charging station that include,
32 without limitation:
33 (a) Establishing limitations on the hours that the electric vehicle charging
34 station may be used;
35 (b) Determining the manner in which users of the electric vehicle charging
36 station are billed for such use; and
37 (c) Establishing any other necessary and appropriate rules or regulations
38 relating to the use of the electric vehicle charging station.
39 4. As used in this section, “electric vehicle charging station” means a
40 station that delivers electricity from a source outside an electric vehicle into one
41 or more electric vehicles. The term includes, without limitation, an electric
42 vehicle charging station where several charge points simultaneously connect
43 several electric vehicles to the station and any related equipment needed to
44 facilitate charging electric vehicles.

